    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-10-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="194"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                <head>194. National Security Action Memorandum No. 263<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d194fn1">Source: Department of State, <gloss target="#t_SS1"
                            >S/S</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files: Lot 72 D 316,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss>s. Top Secret; Eyes Only. The
                        Director of Central Intelligence and the Administrator of <gloss
                            target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> also received copies. Also printed in
                        United States-Vietnam Relations, 1945-1967, Book 12, p. 578.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1963-10-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 11, 1963</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff</item>
                </list>
                <pb facs="0422" n="396" xml:id="pg_396"/>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>South Vietnam</item>
                </list>
                <p>At a meeting on October 5, 1963,<note n="2" xml:id="d194fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d179">Document 179</ref>.</note> the President considered the
                    recommendations contained in the report of Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName> and General <persName
                        corresp="#p_TGMD1">Taylor</persName> on their mission to South Vietnam.</p>
                <p>The President approved the military recommendations contained in Section I B
                    (1-3) of the report, but directed that no formal announcement be made of the
                    implementation of plans to withdraw 1,000 U.S. military personnel by the end of
                    1963.</p>
                <p>After discussion of the remaining recommendations of the report, the President
                    approved an instruction to Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1"
                        >Lodge</persName> which is set forth in State Department telegram No. 534 to
                        Saigon.<note n="3" xml:id="d194fn3">
                        <ref target="#d181">Document 181</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">McGeorge Bundy</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
